1
00:00:11,636 --> 00:00:12,929
Should I open it?

2
00:00:13,013 --> 00:00:15,724
No. I'll do it if you're scared.

3
00:00:17,392 --> 00:00:19,102
I'm not scared.

4
00:00:36,244 --> 00:00:37,787
-I passed.
-Huh?

5
00:00:38,621 --> 00:00:39,956
I passed!

6
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:44,210
Sorry!

7
00:00:44,294 --> 00:00:47,172
-Congrats, Johan!
-Look at Kanau. Congrats!

8
00:00:47,255 --> 00:00:48,089
It's a miracle!

9
00:00:48,173 --> 00:00:49,716
Sorry, Kanau.

10
00:00:49,799 --> 00:00:53,553
Man, I was worried because you said
your working holiday visa might expire.

11
00:00:53,636 --> 00:00:56,806
Wait, so if you pass
your college entrance exams…

12
00:00:56,890 --> 00:00:58,808
You can stay in Japan forever.

13
00:00:58,892 --> 00:01:00,894
I still have a long way to go.

14
00:01:02,353 --> 00:01:03,813
-We were loud, huh?
-Sorry.

15
00:01:03,897 --> 00:01:06,608
-Let's get you some milk.
-Yes, milk.

16
00:01:07,901 --> 00:01:09,069
There, there.

17
00:01:09,152 --> 00:01:09,986
Kanau.

18
00:01:10,070 --> 00:01:13,406
Come on. Time for some celebratory milk.

19
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:19,204
Let's go to Mommy.
All right, we'll go to Mommy.

20
00:01:19,287 --> 00:01:21,498
See, she stopped crying.

21
00:01:23,666 --> 00:01:27,253
We usually only hire university graduates.

22
00:01:29,839 --> 00:01:32,634
I made an exception for you
because you're handsome.

23
00:01:33,968 --> 00:01:38,181
Make sure you get into university
and become a popular teacher, okay?

24
00:01:38,264 --> 00:01:39,099
Here.

25
00:01:41,101 --> 00:01:42,852
I'll do my very best.

26
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:48,566
INSTRUCTOR
HWANG JOHAN

27
00:01:52,904 --> 00:01:54,572
Don't drink too much.

28
00:01:56,699 --> 00:01:58,660
I'm not drinking too much.

29
00:02:00,537 --> 00:02:02,122
You really worked hard.

30
00:02:03,289 --> 00:02:05,792
Sua was shocked too.

31
00:02:06,751 --> 00:02:10,421
She said she had no idea
her brother was this good at studying.

32
00:02:12,340 --> 00:02:13,967
Me too, to be honest.

33
00:02:22,433 --> 00:02:23,852
Well, I worked hard.

34
00:02:25,186 --> 00:02:28,022
Yeah. I really think you did.

35
00:02:39,993 --> 00:02:41,953
I guess I'll go easy on the drinks.

36
00:02:42,453 --> 00:02:43,955
Kanau's waiting for me.

37
00:02:44,038 --> 00:02:45,456
She's waiting for me.

38
00:02:47,292 --> 00:02:48,459
No, me.

39
00:02:49,794 --> 00:02:51,337
-Excuse me.
-Yes?

40
00:02:51,421 --> 00:02:52,839
Check, please.

41
00:02:53,631 --> 00:02:57,844
DAYCARECENTERS.COM

42
00:03:01,514 --> 00:03:02,849
Ryu.

43
00:03:02,932 --> 00:03:03,933
Hm?

44
00:03:06,603 --> 00:03:07,687
One of these days,

45
00:03:09,355 --> 00:03:12,108
I'm thinking of going to see
daycares for Kanau.

46
00:03:12,775 --> 00:03:13,776
Huh?

47
00:03:14,777 --> 00:03:17,655
But Kanau's only three months old.

48
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:19,324
I know.

49
00:03:19,407 --> 00:03:24,829
But it's actually easier
to get into daycare at age zero.

50
00:03:25,914 --> 00:03:29,918
Well, I've kind of looked into it too.

51
00:03:33,546 --> 00:03:38,134
I've been thinking about
going back to work too.

52
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:42,722
Like you and Johan.

53
00:03:43,723 --> 00:03:45,266
Everyone's working hard.

54
00:03:46,517 --> 00:03:48,102
So are you.

55
00:03:56,486 --> 00:03:58,279
I love Kanau.

56
00:04:00,448 --> 00:04:01,908
From the bottom of my heart.

57
00:04:04,619 --> 00:04:05,620
But…

58
00:04:06,537 --> 00:04:09,040
I want to work hard at my job too.

59
00:04:14,003 --> 00:04:15,588
Am I being selfish?

60
00:04:15,672 --> 00:04:17,173
No.

61
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:19,676
Of course not.

62
00:04:21,010 --> 00:04:27,433
Let's not hold back when it comes to
Kanau, work, and our future.

63
00:04:28,017 --> 00:04:31,604
We'll work hard and go for it all.

64
00:04:35,775 --> 00:04:36,985
Thank you.

65
00:04:39,153 --> 00:04:41,948
-"Company employee" is fine, right?
-Yeah.

66
00:04:43,574 --> 00:04:47,662
RYU NARUTAKI, ROOMMATE
HWANG JOHAN, ROOMMATE

67
00:04:47,745 --> 00:04:49,372
Do you think she'll get in?

68
00:04:50,331 --> 00:04:51,457
Let's hope for it.

69
00:04:58,339 --> 00:04:59,757
Hello.

70
00:04:59,841 --> 00:05:01,092
-Hello.
-Hello.

71
00:05:01,175 --> 00:05:02,427
This way.

72
00:05:05,138 --> 00:05:08,266
-Thank you for coming.
-Yes, thank you.

73
00:05:08,349 --> 00:05:09,809
Thank you!

74
00:05:09,892 --> 00:05:11,853
-Bye-bye!
-Bye-bye!

75
00:05:18,067 --> 00:05:21,029
Ms. Aizawa, thank you for waiting.
Please come in.

76
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:31,164
The performance will be
a fun event for all the children.

77
00:05:31,247 --> 00:05:34,167
We warmly welcome parents
to take part too.

78
00:05:35,376 --> 00:05:38,880
May I ask you one final question?

79
00:05:38,963 --> 00:05:39,964
Yes.

80
00:05:41,049 --> 00:05:45,803
I understand that
all of you are roommates.

81
00:05:45,887 --> 00:05:49,724
Um, what exactly is
your relationship to each other?

82
00:05:50,308 --> 00:05:53,603
I'd like to check
because this becomes relevant

83
00:05:53,686 --> 00:05:57,398
for authorized pickup,
as I mentioned earlier.

84
00:05:57,899 --> 00:06:00,526
Well, you see,

85
00:06:00,610 --> 00:06:04,989
these two are helping me raise her.

86
00:06:05,782 --> 00:06:07,200
Our "relationship"?

87
00:06:07,283 --> 00:06:08,701
Um…

88
00:06:08,785 --> 00:06:11,037
-May I say something?
-Yes.

89
00:06:12,622 --> 00:06:14,082
We…

90
00:06:15,792 --> 00:06:19,837
We'd like to become
Kanau's guardians if possible.

91
00:06:21,005 --> 00:06:24,425
We wrote "roommates"
on the application form,

92
00:06:24,926 --> 00:06:27,261
but we're not just living together.

93
00:06:28,221 --> 00:06:30,807
We may not be her parents,

94
00:06:31,557 --> 00:06:33,518
but we're serious.

95
00:06:34,769 --> 00:06:35,853
He's right.

96
00:06:35,937 --> 00:06:38,689
We are taking this seriously.

97
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:43,444
Well, it might seem unusual,

98
00:06:43,528 --> 00:06:47,824
and I understand that
three guardians might sound strange.

99
00:06:48,324 --> 00:06:51,452
I don't think it's strange at all.

100
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:57,250
I'd say we consider it
a unique family environment,

101
00:06:57,333 --> 00:07:00,461
but just because it's unique
doesn't mean it's bad.

102
00:07:01,629 --> 00:07:02,630
Right?

103
00:07:03,214 --> 00:07:04,215
Yes.

104
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:14,350
This is a nice daycare center.

105
00:07:14,851 --> 00:07:15,852
Hm?

106
00:07:17,770 --> 00:07:19,772
I'm saying it's a nice place.

107
00:07:20,481 --> 00:07:23,609
Sumiko is back from maternity leave.

108
00:07:23,693 --> 00:07:24,652
Yes!

109
00:07:26,154 --> 00:07:26,988
Thank you.

110
00:07:27,071 --> 00:07:29,824
-You’re still gorgeous, even as a mom.
-Knock it off!

111
00:07:29,907 --> 00:07:32,243
-How have you been, Ms. Aizawa?
-I'm doing great.

112
00:07:32,326 --> 00:07:33,828
Welcome back, Sumi.

113
00:07:33,911 --> 00:07:34,912
Thanks.

114
00:07:34,996 --> 00:07:38,082
Sorry to jump right in,
but can I get your advice?

115
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:40,084
Straight to business, huh? Sure.

116
00:07:40,168 --> 00:07:43,379
It's about the buttons
on the chest of this dress.

117
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:44,464
Okay.

118
00:07:54,432 --> 00:07:56,309
All right. Let's go drinking.

119
00:07:56,392 --> 00:07:57,727
Good work today.

120
00:07:58,811 --> 00:08:02,106
You made sure to book a place
that has soju, right?

121
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:04,525
I made sure to check.

122
00:08:04,609 --> 00:08:05,776
Good work.

123
00:08:05,860 --> 00:08:08,362
Phew, I'm tired.

124
00:08:08,446 --> 00:08:09,739
Good work today.

125
00:08:09,822 --> 00:08:10,948
You too, Mr. Johan.

126
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:14,285
Johan, you too. Hurry up and let's go.

127
00:08:15,119 --> 00:08:17,079
No, I'll pass today.

128
00:08:17,163 --> 00:08:20,166
Come on, you're no fun.
You didn't come last time either.

129
00:08:22,001 --> 00:08:23,628
I have to go pick up my kid.

130
00:08:23,711 --> 00:08:26,088
What? You have a kid, Mr. Johan?

131
00:08:27,381 --> 00:08:29,008
Yes, I do.

132
00:08:31,177 --> 00:08:33,638
Then take your kid home and join us later.

133
00:08:33,721 --> 00:08:35,223
Leave your kid to your wife.

134
00:08:35,306 --> 00:08:39,352
I don't have money to go drinking.
If I did, I'd save it for my kid.

135
00:08:42,855 --> 00:08:45,358
-What's keeping you? Hurry up.
-Okay.

136
00:08:53,658 --> 00:08:54,867
Mr. Johan.

137
00:08:55,826 --> 00:08:59,580
If you're ever in need of money,
let me know.

138
00:09:00,164 --> 00:09:00,998
What?

139
00:09:01,082 --> 00:09:06,671
We're comrades.
We help each other in times of need.

140
00:09:13,844 --> 00:09:15,555
Hello.

141
00:09:15,638 --> 00:09:18,224
Oh, your pickup is here.

142
00:09:18,307 --> 00:09:20,643
There we go. Okay.

143
00:09:21,894 --> 00:09:23,729
Hello.

144
00:09:25,982 --> 00:09:29,485
-Kanau!
-She was in a good mood all day.

145
00:09:29,569 --> 00:09:31,028
Kanau.

146
00:09:32,321 --> 00:09:33,656
Hello.

147
00:09:34,532 --> 00:09:37,034
-All right, here you go.
-Thank you.

148
00:09:37,118 --> 00:09:39,412
Goodbye, Kanau.

149
00:09:39,495 --> 00:09:44,542
Kanau.

150
00:09:44,625 --> 00:09:46,168
You're not cold?

151
00:09:50,506 --> 00:09:52,258
Kanau, we're almost home.

152
00:09:52,925 --> 00:09:56,178
We're almost home, Kanau.

153
00:10:05,646 --> 00:10:08,107
-Hey, close the door.
-Okay.

154
00:10:10,985 --> 00:10:12,320
How's your fever?

155
00:10:12,403 --> 00:10:15,072
-It's gone down.
-Good.

156
00:10:15,156 --> 00:10:16,032
Yeah.

157
00:10:16,115 --> 00:10:18,659
All right. Here.

158
00:10:19,702 --> 00:10:20,911
Let's see.

159
00:10:21,871 --> 00:10:24,206
It hasn't gone down at all.

160
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:27,251
You better take work off today.

161
00:10:27,335 --> 00:10:28,961
Okay.

162
00:10:33,049 --> 00:10:34,342
Whoa.

163
00:10:35,343 --> 00:10:36,761
And go see a doctor.

164
00:10:37,261 --> 00:10:40,056
If you want,
I can ask to take the day off too.

165
00:10:40,139 --> 00:10:42,308
-I can come with you--
-You're overreacting.

166
00:10:42,975 --> 00:10:44,602
It's just a cold.

167
00:10:44,685 --> 00:10:46,354
You don't know that.

168
00:10:46,437 --> 00:10:49,690
Even young people
can catch all sorts of illnesses.

169
00:10:49,774 --> 00:10:51,567
Yeah, yeah, Doctor.

170
00:10:52,068 --> 00:10:54,236
Doctor, huh?

171
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:55,154
Here.

172
00:10:58,658 --> 00:10:59,659
Ouch.

173
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:09,794
What's this?

174
00:11:09,877 --> 00:11:10,961
Rice porridge.

175
00:11:13,005 --> 00:11:14,674
-Can you eat?
-Yeah.

176
00:11:16,133 --> 00:11:17,885
Careful, it's hot.

177
00:11:19,428 --> 00:11:20,429
Here.

178
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:28,688
We got a bit carried away
since we moved in with Kanau and Sumiko.

179
00:11:30,981 --> 00:11:32,358
That's true.

180
00:11:52,753 --> 00:11:54,171
Not bad, I guess.

181
00:11:56,132 --> 00:11:58,175
-You know what?
-What?

182
00:11:58,801 --> 00:11:59,760
Sumiko made that.

183
00:12:13,816 --> 00:12:18,446
<i>Mr. Hwang Johan.</i>
<i>Please enter Exam Room One.</i>

184
00:12:24,869 --> 00:12:26,746
So…

185
00:12:27,371 --> 00:12:29,373
I think it's just a cold.

186
00:12:29,457 --> 00:12:30,666
Okay.

187
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:32,585
I'll put you on some medicine.

188
00:12:33,169 --> 00:12:34,795
Thank you.

189
00:12:35,337 --> 00:12:37,631
Oh, hold on a minute.

190
00:12:38,299 --> 00:12:39,884
Well, um…

191
00:12:39,967 --> 00:12:43,596
There's something else
that caught my attention.

192
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:47,600
You wrote on your questionnaire
about some numbness in your body.

193
00:12:47,683 --> 00:12:48,809
Yes.

194
00:12:48,893 --> 00:12:51,479
Would you like to get that tested,
just in case?

195
00:12:53,355 --> 00:12:54,732
-Okay.
-Yeah?

196
00:12:55,232 --> 00:12:57,359
Then we'll draw some blood

197
00:12:57,860 --> 00:13:01,113
and look into the numbness in your body.

198
00:13:09,955 --> 00:13:10,790
FUMIE SASAKI

199
00:13:10,873 --> 00:13:13,959
We've done everything we can.

200
00:13:14,585 --> 00:13:20,424
But we must also consider
the other residents' lifestyles.

201
00:13:21,759 --> 00:13:27,223
With ongoing issues and complaints
from other residents and their families,

202
00:13:27,306 --> 00:13:33,187
we have no choice
but to ask her to vacate the facility.

203
00:13:33,270 --> 00:13:36,023
But it'll be worse if we take her home.

204
00:13:36,106 --> 00:13:39,360
Even professional caregivers struggle,
and we're not even trained.

205
00:13:39,443 --> 00:13:46,116
We will provide support
in finding a facility for Ms. Sasaki.

206
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:48,744
We're the ones paying you though.

207
00:13:50,329 --> 00:13:54,959
When you're caring for your own parent,
does it matter if you're a professional?

208
00:14:09,139 --> 00:14:10,349
There we go.

209
00:14:11,851 --> 00:14:13,185
What's wrong?

210
00:14:15,062 --> 00:14:16,188
-Is she awake?
-Yeah.

211
00:14:16,272 --> 00:14:17,398
Oh, she is.

212
00:14:19,817 --> 00:14:21,485
I'm home.

213
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:23,487
She's laughing.

214
00:14:23,571 --> 00:14:25,614
Welcome home.

215
00:14:25,698 --> 00:14:27,700
You drank a lot of milk.

216
00:14:27,783 --> 00:14:28,701
Are you full?

217
00:14:28,784 --> 00:14:30,119
You're full, aren't you?

218
00:14:30,202 --> 00:14:31,787
You're so chatty.

219
00:14:34,123 --> 00:14:34,957
I'll wash this.

220
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:36,584
Thanks.

221
00:14:38,544 --> 00:14:39,753
How's Johan?

222
00:14:40,254 --> 00:14:42,214
He's home.
The doctor said it's just a cold.

223
00:14:42,298 --> 00:14:43,799
Okay.

224
00:14:45,342 --> 00:14:47,761
Is he still holed up in his room?

225
00:14:47,845 --> 00:14:50,764
Yeah. He said better safe than sorry.

226
00:14:58,314 --> 00:14:59,690
I'm coming in.

227
00:15:06,238 --> 00:15:08,699
How long are you gonna
stay shut up in here?

228
00:15:09,617 --> 00:15:11,952
At least until tomorrow.

229
00:15:12,661 --> 00:15:14,371
It's just a cold, right?

230
00:15:14,455 --> 00:15:17,541
That was what I said, wasn't it?

231
00:15:19,126 --> 00:15:21,879
So, did you wash your hands?

232
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:24,173
I did.

233
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:27,718
Did you gargle?

234
00:15:29,011 --> 00:15:30,387
Not yet.

235
00:15:30,888 --> 00:15:33,682
I always tell you to gargle
after you wash your hands--

236
00:15:33,766 --> 00:15:37,603
Yes, okay. I'm very sorry.

237
00:15:37,686 --> 00:15:39,188
-Hey.
-What?

238
00:15:39,271 --> 00:15:40,689
Close the door.

239
00:15:42,274 --> 00:15:43,984
Hey, you!

240
00:15:49,073 --> 00:15:50,366
Don't mess with me.

241
00:16:02,461 --> 00:16:04,213
So, I was thinking…

242
00:16:04,296 --> 00:16:08,676
It would be nice if we could express
this kind of image in that space.

243
00:16:08,759 --> 00:16:11,178
-Yeah.
-I agree.

244
00:16:13,180 --> 00:16:14,640
For example…

245
00:16:15,891 --> 00:16:18,811
We could incorporate a color like this.

246
00:16:18,894 --> 00:16:21,063
This emphasizes the seasonal theme.

247
00:16:21,146 --> 00:16:23,315
-True.
-That's wonderful.

248
00:16:23,399 --> 00:16:26,527
So, should we go ahead
with this color for the walls?

249
00:16:26,610 --> 00:16:28,320
Yeah, for now.

250
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:30,823
I think we can move forward with this.

251
00:16:30,906 --> 00:16:33,534
-Sorry, just a moment.
-Sure.

252
00:16:33,617 --> 00:16:34,451
Hello?

253
00:16:34,535 --> 00:16:37,663
<i>Hello? Ms. Aizawa, sorry to bother you.</i>

254
00:16:37,746 --> 00:16:40,374
<i>Kanau has a fever.</i>

255
00:16:40,457 --> 00:16:41,709
Oh.

256
00:16:41,792 --> 00:16:44,294
<i>Could you please come pick her up?</i>

257
00:16:44,378 --> 00:16:46,922
Oh, um…

258
00:16:47,006 --> 00:16:51,635
<i>We ask that children be picked up</i>
<i>if their temperature goes over 37.5°C.</i>

259
00:16:51,719 --> 00:16:54,722
Right. Um, I'll head over.

260
00:16:54,805 --> 00:16:57,516
My meeting should be over
in about an hour.

261
00:17:11,530 --> 00:17:14,324
-Hello?
<i>-Hello? Ms. Aizawa?</i>

262
00:17:14,408 --> 00:17:18,454
-Speaking.
-<i>Um, Kanau has a fever again.</i>

263
00:17:18,537 --> 00:17:21,040
<i>Can you come pick her up?</i>

264
00:17:22,249 --> 00:17:25,044
Yes. I'll be right there.

265
00:17:25,127 --> 00:17:26,795
-I have a suggestion.
-Yeah?

266
00:17:26,879 --> 00:17:30,799
What if we completely open up
this shoulder area?

267
00:17:32,593 --> 00:17:33,761
I see.

268
00:17:33,844 --> 00:17:36,180
You're right. That might work.

269
00:17:36,263 --> 00:17:39,016
-From around here.
-Yeah.

270
00:17:39,099 --> 00:17:40,976
-That's nice.
-Yeah.

271
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:43,228
-It looks good.
-Yeah.

272
00:17:47,399 --> 00:17:49,818
Go ahead and take it.
It's the daycare, right?

273
00:17:55,032 --> 00:17:56,366
Hello?

274
00:17:56,450 --> 00:18:00,537
"I have plans with a friend in Tokyo."

275
00:18:00,621 --> 00:18:05,000
-"I have plans with a friend in Tokyo."
-Good.

276
00:18:05,084 --> 00:18:09,296
Now, please practice this with each other.

277
00:18:09,379 --> 00:18:10,798
-Okay.
-Okay.

278
00:18:12,174 --> 00:18:13,425
Hello?

279
00:18:13,926 --> 00:18:15,886
-<i>Oh, sorry, Johan.</i>
<i>-</i>Yeah.

280
00:18:15,969 --> 00:18:18,639
<i>I got a call that Kanau has a fever again.</i>

281
00:18:19,139 --> 00:18:21,433
<i>Can you go pick her up?</i>

282
00:18:21,517 --> 00:18:23,602
<i>I really can't leave work today.</i>

283
00:18:23,685 --> 00:18:26,063
Ah, okay.

284
00:18:26,146 --> 00:18:29,983
I'll try asking if I can leave
in about 30 minutes.

285
00:18:30,484 --> 00:18:33,278
Yeah. No, it's fine.

286
00:18:33,362 --> 00:18:35,030
It's tough for Ryu.

287
00:18:35,114 --> 00:18:40,285
Caregivers have stricter rules.
Unlike me, he can't check his phone.

288
00:18:40,369 --> 00:18:41,787
We're lifting you up.

289
00:18:41,870 --> 00:18:43,789
Here. We're lifting you up now.

290
00:18:45,541 --> 00:18:47,084
There we go.

291
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:52,214
Can you see the ocean, Ms. Sasaki?

292
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:55,843
Ms. Sasaki, I know
you used to like this place.

293
00:18:58,428 --> 00:19:00,389
Can you see the ocean?

294
00:19:01,932 --> 00:19:03,267
There we go.

295
00:19:05,811 --> 00:19:07,521
It's beautiful.

296
00:19:21,785 --> 00:19:24,079
You're quiet today, aren't you?

297
00:19:34,339 --> 00:19:36,758
Mister?

298
00:19:37,259 --> 00:19:38,260
Hm?

299
00:19:41,722 --> 00:19:45,017
The thing about life is…

300
00:19:47,352 --> 00:19:51,523
There’s nothing you can
really do about it.

301
00:19:54,193 --> 00:19:55,194
Huh?

302
00:20:03,243 --> 00:20:07,456
Such sad sounds.

303
00:20:15,464 --> 00:20:18,133
So many things…

304
00:20:20,177 --> 00:20:25,015
just pass you by.

305
00:20:28,268 --> 00:20:29,895
But you know?

306
00:20:32,272 --> 00:20:38,028
There are also things that never change.

307
00:20:45,035 --> 00:20:46,411
Um…

308
00:20:51,458 --> 00:20:54,628
Thank you…

309
00:20:56,713 --> 00:20:59,758
for bringing me here.

310
00:21:05,722 --> 00:21:06,932
Sure.

311
00:21:23,156 --> 00:21:24,741
I'm home.

312
00:21:24,825 --> 00:21:26,785
-Welcome home.
-Welcome home.

313
00:21:29,496 --> 00:21:32,958
Sorry I've been getting home late
every day recently.

314
00:21:33,834 --> 00:21:37,337
Ms. Sasaki, was it?
Did you find her next nursing home?

315
00:21:37,421 --> 00:21:42,217
Not yet. I've been looking around
with my coworker, but it's not easy.

316
00:21:44,052 --> 00:21:45,595
The bath is ready.

317
00:21:45,679 --> 00:21:46,680
Okay.

318
00:21:48,390 --> 00:21:50,809
I guess I'll go take a bath now.

319
00:22:19,379 --> 00:22:21,506
Sumiko. Wanna drink this?

320
00:22:22,466 --> 00:22:23,633
Thanks.

321
00:22:24,301 --> 00:22:25,761
-I'll leave it here.
-Okay.

322
00:22:32,476 --> 00:22:34,394
Thanks for picking her up today.

323
00:22:36,229 --> 00:22:38,231
Call me anytime.

324
00:22:38,315 --> 00:22:43,779
If you want, we could ask the principal
to always call me.

325
00:22:43,862 --> 00:22:44,946
Ask the principal?

326
00:22:45,030 --> 00:22:46,990
Yeah. Why not?

327
00:22:58,377 --> 00:23:00,295
Wow, that's amazing.

328
00:23:00,379 --> 00:23:02,547
Kanau. Come here.

329
00:23:03,548 --> 00:23:05,467
All right. There, there.

330
00:23:11,556 --> 00:23:16,269
Kanau, my dear Kanau.

331
00:23:16,353 --> 00:23:18,063
Peekaboo.

332
00:23:19,898 --> 00:23:22,651
Kanau.

333
00:23:26,113 --> 00:23:29,324
Sorry. Just hang with me a bit longer.

334
00:23:30,784 --> 00:23:32,285
Mr. Hwang.

335
00:23:32,369 --> 00:23:34,037
Mr. Hwang Johan.

336
00:23:34,121 --> 00:23:35,038
Yes?

337
00:23:35,122 --> 00:23:36,456
Please come this way.

338
00:23:41,169 --> 00:23:42,754
Let's go.

339
00:23:43,713 --> 00:23:46,133
I didn't know you had a child.

340
00:23:46,633 --> 00:23:47,717
I do.

341
00:23:47,801 --> 00:23:49,845
I'm Kanau!

342
00:23:51,221 --> 00:23:53,056
So, Mr. Hwang.

343
00:23:53,974 --> 00:23:56,601
Your blood test didn't show any issues.

344
00:23:56,685 --> 00:23:59,062
But, well…

345
00:24:00,021 --> 00:24:03,650
These are the results
from your electromyography test.

346
00:24:05,235 --> 00:24:06,695
ALS.

347
00:24:07,195 --> 00:24:10,365
Or it could be SBMA.

348
00:24:10,991 --> 00:24:13,618
They are hard to distinguish.

349
00:24:14,286 --> 00:24:17,497
But there is a possibility
it could be an intractable disease.

350
00:24:19,624 --> 00:24:22,627
Oh, um…

351
00:24:24,588 --> 00:24:29,468
What are ALS and SBMA?

352
00:24:29,551 --> 00:24:30,886
With either condition,

353
00:24:30,969 --> 00:24:35,056
the muscles in your entire body
will incrementally stop moving.

354
00:24:35,724 --> 00:24:39,895
And eventually,
you won't be able to breathe on your own.

355
00:24:40,395 --> 00:24:41,855
It is a progressive disease.

356
00:24:50,822 --> 00:24:52,699
It can be cured, right?

357
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,868
At this stage,

358
00:24:55,619 --> 00:24:59,789
I'm sorry to say that
there is no cure for this disease.

359
00:25:01,583 --> 00:25:03,668
For diseases like this,

360
00:25:03,752 --> 00:25:09,466
we recommend that you get tested
and treated in your home country.

361
00:25:11,593 --> 00:25:14,304
Not only because of medical costs,

362
00:25:15,388 --> 00:25:19,267
but also because support from your family
will be extremely important.

363
00:25:21,603 --> 00:25:22,687
What do you think?

364
00:25:23,563 --> 00:25:26,358
Why don't you consider
getting treatment in Korea?

365
00:25:36,076 --> 00:25:37,661
Chubby?

366
00:25:38,286 --> 00:25:40,747
-Chubby.
-Chubby.

367
00:25:41,540 --> 00:25:43,083
Oh, sorry.

368
00:25:44,167 --> 00:25:46,169
-Ryu.
-Yeah?

369
00:25:46,253 --> 00:25:48,338
You have an early shift tomorrow, right?

370
00:25:48,421 --> 00:25:49,422
Yeah.

371
00:25:50,423 --> 00:25:53,218
Can you pick up Kanau?

372
00:25:53,301 --> 00:25:54,553
Of course.

373
00:25:55,929 --> 00:25:58,223
Uncle Ryu's gonna pick you up tomorrow.

374
00:25:58,306 --> 00:26:01,268
-Isn't that great?
-Woo-hoo!

375
00:26:01,810 --> 00:26:03,061
Sorry.

376
00:26:03,895 --> 00:26:08,108
I might be too busy
to pick her up for a while.

377
00:26:08,191 --> 00:26:09,609
Studying for your exams?

378
00:26:11,570 --> 00:26:12,571
Yeah.

379
00:26:13,405 --> 00:26:15,448
Good luck.

380
00:26:25,792 --> 00:26:29,212
It's rare for you to call me over.

381
00:26:31,339 --> 00:26:33,133
Wow.

382
00:26:33,216 --> 00:26:35,176
I didn't know about this place.

383
00:26:52,027 --> 00:26:53,486
You mentioned before

384
00:26:55,238 --> 00:26:57,073
about helping if I ever needed money.

385
00:26:57,157 --> 00:26:58,700
Oh, yes.

386
00:26:58,783 --> 00:27:00,410
What about it?

387
00:27:02,329 --> 00:27:04,122
What exactly did you mean?

388
00:27:06,750 --> 00:27:11,755
Okay, this round's on the house!

389
00:27:17,761 --> 00:27:18,720
-Ready?
-Ready?

390
00:27:18,803 --> 00:27:21,556
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

391
00:27:39,741 --> 00:27:42,827
Why don't you try calling him
if you're that worried?

392
00:27:43,578 --> 00:27:45,330
Well…

393
00:27:45,413 --> 00:27:47,540
He must be busy with this and that.

394
00:27:51,586 --> 00:27:53,630
You had a lot to drink, huh?

395
00:27:53,713 --> 00:27:55,882
Are you okay?

396
00:27:55,965 --> 00:28:00,720
Oh, no. You can't do that here.

397
00:28:02,722 --> 00:28:05,016
But it was fun, wasn't it?

398
00:28:05,100 --> 00:28:06,851
-Wait.
-Oh.

399
00:28:12,649 --> 00:28:13,775
Hello?

400
00:28:14,359 --> 00:28:15,819
-<i>Hello!</i>
-Hello?

401
00:28:16,319 --> 00:28:17,153
Huh?

402
00:28:17,237 --> 00:28:19,406
-Um…
-<i>Are you from Mr. Johan's household?</i>

403
00:28:19,489 --> 00:28:21,700
-Uh, yes. Who is this?
-<i>Oh, sorry.</i>

404
00:28:21,783 --> 00:28:25,578
<i>Mr. Johan kinda got drunk</i>
<i>and passed out tonight.</i>

405
00:28:25,662 --> 00:28:26,705
What?

406
00:28:26,788 --> 00:28:30,041
Oh, uh, I'll come pick him up then.

407
00:28:30,125 --> 00:28:31,042
<i>It's okay.</i>

408
00:28:31,126 --> 00:28:32,919
<i>I live nearby, so he can stay over.</i>

409
00:28:33,002 --> 00:28:35,505
Oh, no. I'd feel bad.

410
00:28:35,588 --> 00:28:37,716
<i>Don't worry about it. Oh!</i>

411
00:28:37,799 --> 00:28:40,427
<i>I-I'll hang up now. Sorry!</i>

412
00:28:40,510 --> 00:28:42,721
Huh? Wait.

413
00:28:42,804 --> 00:28:44,222
<i>Mr. Johan!</i>

414
00:29:06,161 --> 00:29:07,370
Sumiko?

415
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:13,460
Kanau has a fever?

416
00:29:14,669 --> 00:29:17,172
Oh, right.

417
00:29:17,255 --> 00:29:21,760
But I'm working this afternoon.

418
00:29:22,677 --> 00:29:25,138
Yeah. What should we do?

419
00:29:26,514 --> 00:29:27,932
Yeah.

420
00:29:29,517 --> 00:29:30,810
Hold on a second.

421
00:29:31,686 --> 00:29:32,937
Mr. Johan.

422
00:29:33,730 --> 00:29:35,940
I'll take over your class for you.

423
00:29:36,441 --> 00:29:38,026
-Really?
-Yes.

424
00:29:38,109 --> 00:29:39,235
Thank you.

425
00:29:39,903 --> 00:29:43,615
Oh, Sumiko. I can go after all.

426
00:29:44,115 --> 00:29:46,075
Yeah. Got it.

427
00:29:48,745 --> 00:29:51,080
-Thank you so much.
-Sure.

428
00:29:51,790 --> 00:29:53,958
-Are you going already?
-Yes, I'll head out.

429
00:29:54,042 --> 00:29:56,711
Mr. Johan, your bag.

430
00:29:58,004 --> 00:29:59,631
-Take care.
-Thanks.

431
00:29:59,714 --> 00:30:01,716
-I'll be off. See you later.
-Okay.

432
00:30:06,429 --> 00:30:07,764
Hello.

433
00:30:13,937 --> 00:30:17,440
Oh, Mr. Johan.
Feels like it's been a while.

434
00:30:17,524 --> 00:30:19,025
Yes, it's been a while.

435
00:30:19,108 --> 00:30:20,693
How's Kanau?

436
00:30:20,777 --> 00:30:21,820
She's okay.

437
00:30:21,903 --> 00:30:23,988
It seems her fever's gone down too.

438
00:30:25,698 --> 00:30:27,867
-Yes?
-I'm opening the door.

439
00:30:30,495 --> 00:30:32,163
Her pickup's here.

440
00:30:33,289 --> 00:30:34,707
Kanau.

441
00:30:34,791 --> 00:30:36,584
She's doing much better.

442
00:30:37,085 --> 00:30:38,294
Kanau.

443
00:30:38,878 --> 00:30:40,880
Are you okay?

444
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:44,843
Thank you.

445
00:30:57,522 --> 00:30:58,731
We're home.

446
00:30:58,815 --> 00:31:01,109
-We're home.
-Welcome home.

447
00:31:06,739 --> 00:31:09,200
-Thanks for today. You saved me.
-No problem.

448
00:31:09,284 --> 00:31:11,536
-Has her fever gone down?
-Yeah, it has.

449
00:31:11,619 --> 00:31:12,829
What a relief.

450
00:31:26,718 --> 00:31:27,552
Hey.

451
00:31:27,635 --> 00:31:29,429
Hey, welcome home.

452
00:31:39,230 --> 00:31:41,065
I'm going out for a bit.

453
00:31:41,149 --> 00:31:42,150
Huh?

454
00:31:55,163 --> 00:31:56,497
Where are you going?

455
00:32:01,586 --> 00:32:03,004
I made plans.

456
00:32:03,087 --> 00:32:04,881
Plans?

457
00:32:10,178 --> 00:32:12,889
You know, like yesterday too.

458
00:32:13,389 --> 00:32:14,807
At least answer your phone.

459
00:32:17,060 --> 00:32:17,894
Sorry.

460
00:32:17,977 --> 00:32:19,979
No. I don't want to hear "sorry."

461
00:32:20,063 --> 00:32:21,064
Sorry.

462
00:32:21,814 --> 00:32:23,524
I'll be sure to answer my phone.

463
00:32:24,525 --> 00:32:26,903
Okay, I'm heading out.

464
00:32:38,247 --> 00:32:42,961
Yes! I'm in a good mood.
This one's on the house today!

465
00:32:54,847 --> 00:32:55,807
What?

466
00:32:55,890 --> 00:32:58,810
You gotta watch out
for punch-drunk syndrome and stuff.

467
00:32:58,893 --> 00:32:59,894
Johan!

468
00:33:04,023 --> 00:33:06,192
You're getting out of shape, huh?

469
00:33:44,605 --> 00:33:45,606
Hm?

470
00:33:48,901 --> 00:33:50,486
You're still awake.

471
00:33:51,904 --> 00:33:53,698
Do you have any idea what time it is?

472
00:33:53,781 --> 00:33:55,575
Hmm.

473
00:34:03,583 --> 00:34:06,669
Oh. It's still only one o'clock.

474
00:34:08,588 --> 00:34:11,007
Sweetfish…

475
00:34:18,931 --> 00:34:22,018
Washing my hands.

476
00:34:22,101 --> 00:34:23,519
-Hey.
-Washing my--

477
00:34:23,603 --> 00:34:26,147
Kanau and Sumiko are sleeping.
Keep it down.

478
00:34:26,230 --> 00:34:27,398
Huh?

479
00:34:27,482 --> 00:34:29,358
They're sleeping.

480
00:34:29,859 --> 00:34:31,319
Oh.

481
00:34:38,326 --> 00:34:43,122
Kanau!

482
00:34:43,206 --> 00:34:44,665
Hey, stop that.

483
00:34:45,333 --> 00:34:47,585
-Stop.
-Huh?

484
00:34:47,668 --> 00:34:49,712
Let go of me!

485
00:34:51,506 --> 00:34:53,466
Over there. Go over there.

486
00:34:53,966 --> 00:34:56,511
Okay, okay.

487
00:35:04,477 --> 00:35:06,270
You're way too drunk.

488
00:35:06,771 --> 00:35:08,106
Damn.

489
00:35:09,023 --> 00:35:10,983
Shut up.

490
00:35:11,067 --> 00:35:12,985
You're the one that needs to shut up.

491
00:35:14,862 --> 00:35:17,281
-What?
-What do you mean "what"?

492
00:35:17,365 --> 00:35:21,327
What's with you?
You've been acting weird lately.

493
00:35:23,621 --> 00:35:26,040
I just went drinking for a bit.

494
00:35:26,124 --> 00:35:28,209
Right now, we need to support each other.

495
00:35:30,044 --> 00:35:32,213
Support each other?

496
00:35:33,131 --> 00:35:34,340
Meanwhile, you…

497
00:35:36,300 --> 00:35:37,927
You rarely pick Kanau up.

498
00:35:38,010 --> 00:35:39,720
That's why I do the housework.

499
00:35:39,804 --> 00:35:41,097
I do it too.

500
00:35:41,681 --> 00:35:43,015
So does Sumiko.

501
00:35:45,726 --> 00:35:49,272
You're the one
who's always coming home late.

502
00:35:49,355 --> 00:35:51,107
You don't answer your phone either.

503
00:35:51,607 --> 00:35:54,986
Sumiko and I are the ones
watching Kanau during that time.

504
00:35:55,069 --> 00:35:56,529
I can't use my phone at work.

505
00:35:56,612 --> 00:35:58,322
We all work!

506
00:36:00,575 --> 00:36:02,326
Keep it down.

507
00:36:13,588 --> 00:36:15,173
I came all the way to Japan.

508
00:36:18,301 --> 00:36:22,138
And you give me a hard time
for going out a few times.

509
00:36:28,227 --> 00:36:30,146
You asked me to come to Japan.

510
00:36:31,314 --> 00:36:32,398
What?

511
00:36:33,274 --> 00:36:35,693
Sumiko and Seiichi.

512
00:36:36,569 --> 00:36:40,031
They were your friends to begin with.

513
00:36:41,699 --> 00:36:43,784
Why would you say it like that?

514
00:36:45,786 --> 00:36:46,829
What?

515
00:36:47,330 --> 00:36:50,082
Are you saying
I dragged you here against your will?

516
00:36:51,500 --> 00:36:53,211
I never said that.

517
00:36:54,128 --> 00:36:59,383
You were in such a bad state,
so I suggested you live here--

518
00:36:59,467 --> 00:37:00,843
Don't look down on me!

519
00:37:02,178 --> 00:37:03,888
I said don't look down on me.

520
00:37:09,310 --> 00:37:10,228
Did you

521
00:37:12,063 --> 00:37:17,068
bring me here out of pity?

522
00:37:19,487 --> 00:37:22,114
This whole time…

523
00:37:24,575 --> 00:37:27,036
did you feel sorry for me?

524
00:37:29,622 --> 00:37:31,332
That wasn't what I meant.

525
00:37:35,544 --> 00:37:36,545
Then…

526
00:37:38,756 --> 00:37:40,466
what did you mean?

527
00:37:41,634 --> 00:37:43,010
It's…

528
00:38:10,246 --> 00:38:12,206
I found someone I care about.

529
00:38:16,544 --> 00:38:17,545
What?

530
00:38:20,673 --> 00:38:22,883
Someone I want to protect.

531
00:38:24,302 --> 00:38:25,469
Someone that means…

532
00:38:28,014 --> 00:38:29,890
more to me than anything else.

533
00:38:33,394 --> 00:38:34,854
I want to…

534
00:38:39,817 --> 00:38:41,444
make that person happy.

535
00:38:42,111 --> 00:38:43,362
No, wait.

536
00:38:46,574 --> 00:38:47,450
What?

537
00:38:47,533 --> 00:38:49,702
W-Wait a minute.

538
00:38:51,412 --> 00:38:52,955
What are you saying?

539
00:38:53,831 --> 00:38:55,291
No way.

540
00:38:55,791 --> 00:38:56,709
What?

541
00:38:57,752 --> 00:38:59,754
I can't believe you're doing this.

542
00:38:59,837 --> 00:39:00,838
I know.

543
00:39:02,757 --> 00:39:03,591
Sorry.

544
00:39:03,674 --> 00:39:05,134
I don't want "sorry."

545
00:39:05,217 --> 00:39:07,928
-Sorry.
-I said stop apologizing!

546
00:39:09,680 --> 00:39:10,681
I'll…

547
00:39:12,516 --> 00:39:13,434
move out.

548
00:39:19,190 --> 00:39:22,818
I enjoyed the time we spent together.

549
00:39:27,698 --> 00:39:30,701
But I can't stay with you anymore.

550
00:41:04,712 --> 00:41:05,713
Bye.

551
00:41:20,728 --> 00:41:23,647
Please throw away the rest of my stuff.

552
00:41:35,159 --> 00:41:36,577
About him…

553
00:41:37,453 --> 00:41:38,662
Take care of him, okay?

554
00:41:43,292 --> 00:41:44,710
Kanau.

555
00:41:49,965 --> 00:41:51,467
Take care.

556
00:41:58,390 --> 00:42:00,142
Thank you for everything.

557
00:46:17,733 --> 00:46:20,652
Subtitle translation by: Remi Miura
